<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1085,1237,1494]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">
This species was described as 
<emphasis box="[494,714,1238,1259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oudemans" authorityYear="1910" box="[494,633,1238,1259]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hauptmannia</taxonomicName>
iranica
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[777,818,1238,1259]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">Iran</collectingCountry>
(HAITLINGER &amp; SABOORI 1996). Later MĄKOL &amp; WOHLTMANN (2012) this species transferred to the genus 
<emphasis box="[178,304,1296,1317]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">
<taxonomicName authorityName="BERLESE" authorityYear="1891" box="[178,300,1296,1317]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Abrolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Abrolophus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Now, based on two palpgenual setae, is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="HAITLINGER" authorityYear="2011" box="[178,333,1325,1346]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[178,333,1325,1346]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">Marantelophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. SABOORI &amp; ATAMEHR (2000) described from 
<collectingCountry box="[887,928,1326,1347]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">Iran</collectingCountry>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamalii">Hauptmannia kamalii</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="HAITLINGER R" box="[267,479,1355,1377]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" pagination="47 - 54" refId="ref2893" refString="HAITLINGER R. (2011 b): A new genus and four new species of erythraeid mites from Indonesia, with new records of the family (Acari: Prostigmata: Erythraeidae). - Rev. Iber. Aracnol. 19: 47 - 54." type="journal article" year="2011">HAITLINGER (2011b)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species, to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="HAITLINGER" authorityYear="2011" box="[864,1018,1355,1376]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,1018,1355,1376]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">Marantelophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later 
<taxonomicName box="[178,291,1384,1406]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamalii">
<emphasis box="[178,291,1384,1406]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">M. kamalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[507,631,1384,1405]" name="Serbia" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
(HAITLINGER &amp; ŠUNDIĆ 2014). Metric and meristic data for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haitlinger" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="HAITLINGER &amp; SABOORI" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[356,475,1414,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[356,475,1414,1435]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">M. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[527,638,1413,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamalii">
<emphasis box="[527,638,1413,1435]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">M. kamalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are identical. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName box="[900,1011,1413,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamalii">
<emphasis box="[900,1011,1413,1435]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">M. kamalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be regarded as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haitlinger" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="HAITLINGER &amp; SABOORI" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[487,606,1443,1464]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[487,606,1443,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">M. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Corrected and new etric data for 
<typeStatus box="[967,1056,1443,1465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haitlinger" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="HAITLINGER &amp; SABOORI" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[178,295,1473,1494]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[178,295,1473,1494]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">M. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are given in Table 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1085,1509,1590]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">
Leg setal formula (
<typeStatus box="[376,471,1509,1531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1189">holotype</typeStatus>
). Leg I: Ta badly visible, 1ω, 2ζ,?; Ti 2φ, 1κ,?12; Ge 1σ, 1κ, 9; Tf 8; Bf 5; Tr 2; Cx 1. Leg II: Ta 1ω, 2ζ, 22; Ti 2φ, 13; Ge 1σ, 1κ, 9; Tf 5; Bf 5; Tr 2; Cx 1. Leg III: Ta 1ζ, 19; Ti 1φ, 13; Ge 1σ, 9; Tf 5; Bf 5; Tr 2; Cx 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,219,475]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">
Specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[361,435,219,240]" name="Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[451,542,219,240]" name="Hungary" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[558,682,219,241]" name="San Marino" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">San Marino</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[744,825,219,241]" name="Ukraine" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
were determined as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M. multisetosus</emphasis>
(ZHANG &amp; Goldarazena 1996) (
<bibRefCitation author="HAITLINGER R" box="[646,847,248,270]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" pagination="107 - 123" refId="ref2628" refString="HAITLINGER R. (2006 a): New records of mites (Acari: Prostigmata: Erythraeidae, Trombidiidae) from Smos, Greece, with descriptions of six new species. - Syst. Appl. &amp; Acarol. 11: 107 - 123." type="journal article" year="2006">HAITLINGER 2006a</bibRefCitation>
, b, 2007, 2008) and 
<specimenCount pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" type="generic">6 specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[347,471,278,299]" name="Serbia" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
as were determined as 
<emphasis box="[712,814,277,299]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M. kamali</emphasis>
i. In key by 
<bibRefCitation author="HAKIMITABAR M &amp; GHOBARI H" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" pagination="225 - 236" refId="ref3480" refString="HAKIMITABAR M., GHOBARI H. &amp; A. SABOORI (2015): New ectoparasitic Abrolophinae mites (Acari, Erythraeidae, Marantelophus) on thrips and aphids (Insecta) from Iran. - Acta Zool. Sci. Hung. 61 (3): 225 - 236." type="journal article" year="2015">HAKIMITABAR et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[314,425,307,328]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamalii">
<emphasis box="[314,335,307,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[349,425,307,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">kamalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[479,639,307,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M. multisetosus</emphasis>
differ in number of normal setae on Ti III (
<specimenCount box="[186,248,336,358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" type="generic">
13 
<taxonomicName box="[219,248,337,358]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Hauptmannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamalii">
<emphasis box="[219,248,337,358]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
kamalii vs. 
<specimenCount box="[373,435,336,358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" type="generic">
11 
<emphasis box="[407,435,337,358]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M.</emphasis>
</specimenCount>
multisetosus). In our collection 
<specimenCount box="[764,902,336,358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" type="generic">18 specimens</specimenCount>
have on Ti III 13 normal setae, 
<specimenCount box="[326,444,365,387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" type="generic">4specimens</specimenCount>
12 setae and 
<specimenCount box="[592,734,365,387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
11 setae. Based on this character and number of dorsal setae less than 160 setae specimens from over mentioned countries are included to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haitlinger" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="HAITLINGER &amp; SABOORI" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[338,455,425,446]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[338,455,425,446]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, is problem with differentiate 
<emphasis box="[874,1033,424,446]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M. multisetosus</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haitlinger" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="HAITLINGER &amp; SABOORI" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[179,296,454,475]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Marantelophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[179,296,454,475]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1190">M. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ti IIII with 12 setae). It should be explained in future.
</paragraph>
